- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of linear recurrent sequences, which are a type of data structure commonly used in algorithm design.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possibility as the paper may involve geometric interpretations of ideals and their primary decompositions.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possibility as the paper may involve the use of linear systems theory in the analysis of the algorithms presented.
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is a possibility as the paper may involve the use of logical reasoning in the design and analysis of the algorithms presented.
